parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Incomplete Recall Repairs for Engine Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or incomplete repair of the engine recall can lead to potential engine failure, stalling, or other safety issues, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to the recall repair process.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the integrated trailer brake control can cause inadequate braking power to the trailer, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: The truck does most of the braking work
anti-lock brakes activate on the truck
inadequate braking from the trailer
no braking power to the trailer when sitting still on a sloped grade.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent starting issue can cause delays, inconvenience, and potential safety risks, especially for commercial drivers who rely on their vehicles for work.
symptoms: The truck takes anywhere from 2 minutes to over 1 hour to restart
only a "click" sound is heard from the starter
all electrical systems in the vehicle seem to be working fine except for the starter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the reductant heater can cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the owner without warranty coverage.
symptoms: The vehicle's emissions system malfunctions
the vehicle fails emissions tests
the reductant heater is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shuttering or slipping can cause the vehicle to shake violently, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission shuttles between gears
the vehicle shakes violently
the transmission slips or hesitates
the issue is more prominent when the engine is cold
the issue occurs when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball hitch weld can cause the trailer to detach from the truck while in motion, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potential damage to the truck, trailer, and surrounding property.
symptoms: The ball hitch comes detached from the truck bed
the trailer neck slams into the center of the bed
the ball hitch falls to the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive paint chipping can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the structural integrity of the vehicle and affecting its overall appearance and resale value.
symptoms: Paint chipping in areas that would not receive normal wear and tear
such as the side of the body and tailgate.
